WEBVTT

00:05.672 --> 00:07.757
[The Bee Gee's "I.O.I.O"]
- ♪ I, O ♪

00:07.841 --> 00:11.219
♪ I, I, I, I, I, I, O ♪

00:11.302 --> 00:13.471
♪ I, O ♪

00:13.555 --> 00:15.140
[people shouting]
♪ I, O ♪

00:15.223 --> 00:18.435
♪ I, I, I, I, I, I, O ♪

00:18.518 --> 00:20.061
♪ I, O ♪

00:20.145 --> 00:23.523
♪ You know I love getting up
in the morning ♪

00:23.606 --> 00:28.778
♪ When the sun first strikes
the trees ♪

00:28.862 --> 00:33.283
♪ All the morning birds
that sing above ♪

00:33.366 --> 00:36.494
♪ Still bring back memories ♪

00:36.578 --> 00:40.206
♪ Of a girl who stood
beside me ♪

00:40.290 --> 00:45.128
♪ When the rights I did
were wrong ♪

00:45.211 --> 00:49.007
♪ But she went
back down the river ♪

00:49.090 --> 00:52.761
♪ Just when I thought
I could be strong ♪

00:52.844 --> 00:57.557
♪ When I thought
I could be strong ♪

00:57.640 --> 01:00.143
♪ So I sing I, O ♪

01:00.226 --> 01:01.561
♪ I, I, I, I, I ♪

01:01.644 --> 01:03.146
- Good morning, sir.

01:03.229 --> 01:05.899
- Good morning.
Thank you.

01:05.982 --> 01:07.400
- ♪ I, O ♪

01:07.484 --> 01:10.862
♪ I, I, I, I, I, I, O ♪

01:10.945 --> 01:12.030
♪ I, O ♪

01:12.113 --> 01:13.239
- Tea, Miss Sykes?

01:13.323 --> 01:15.450
- No, thank you, Mr. Chadley.

01:15.533 --> 01:16.701
Soon as she's asleep,

01:16.785 --> 01:18.244
I'll be out like a light
myself.

01:18.328 --> 01:20.705
- I will be quiet as the mouse.

01:20.789 --> 01:22.791
Babies must be very tiresome.

01:22.874 --> 01:25.168
- Mm. Don't get me started.

01:25.251 --> 01:27.670
You wake me if my sister calls,
though, won't you?

01:27.754 --> 01:29.005
- Mm.

01:29.088 --> 01:31.549
[tense music]

01:31.633 --> 01:33.051
Oh.

01:33.134 --> 01:39.390
♪ ♪

01:39.474 --> 01:41.476
[phone ringing]
[baby crying]

01:41.559 --> 01:43.269
Sorry. Sorry.

01:44.771 --> 01:47.816
[phone ringing]
[baby crying]

01:47.899 --> 01:51.236
Good morning.
Pennyworth Security.

01:51.319 --> 01:53.154
- This is Lucius Fox.

01:53.238 --> 01:55.240
[muffled] Lucius Fox.

01:55.323 --> 01:57.909
Mayday. Mayday.

01:57.992 --> 02:00.119
[electronic beeping]

02:00.203 --> 02:01.788
[muffled] Level 7.
- Hello?

02:01.871 --> 02:05.166
- Level 7. I repeat, Level 7.

02:05.250 --> 02:06.376
Mayday.

02:06.459 --> 02:09.546
- Did you say Level 7,
Dr. Fox?

02:09.629 --> 02:12.006
Hello? Can you hear me?

02:12.090 --> 02:13.383
[sparks burst]

02:13.466 --> 02:15.134
[suspenseful music]

02:15.218 --> 02:16.553
♪ ♪

02:16.636 --> 02:18.429
- Darn.
- Fair do.

02:18.513 --> 02:22.225
I thought you were all mouth,
but the bugger worked.

02:22.308 --> 02:24.561
You're a wizard, you are.
- Ow.

02:24.644 --> 02:26.104
- Alfie.

02:26.187 --> 02:28.523
♪ ♪

02:28.606 --> 02:29.941
[baby crying]
Dash and buggery!

02:30.024 --> 02:32.068
- Call that quiet, do you?

02:32.151 --> 02:33.945
- Sorry.
- Shh.

02:34.028 --> 02:35.446
[baby cries]

02:35.530 --> 02:37.073
- Thank you
for your assistance, Inspector.

02:37.156 --> 02:38.241
We'll wait to hear from you.

02:38.324 --> 02:39.325
- Of course.
Pennyworth.

02:39.409 --> 02:40.743
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

02:40.827 --> 02:42.912
- Thank you, Inspector.

02:42.996 --> 02:44.622
- All good?
- Sorted.

02:44.706 --> 02:46.040
- Tea's ready
if you'd like some.

02:46.124 --> 02:48.626
Milk and sugar are on the tray.

02:48.710 --> 02:50.295
- Oh, thanks, Gladys,

02:50.378 --> 02:52.964
but I think we're all ready
to hit the sack.

02:53.047 --> 02:55.008
- Uh, she means sleep.

02:55.091 --> 02:57.510
I think we're exhausted.
- I'm wide awake.

02:57.594 --> 02:58.845
[phone ringing]
- No you're not.

02:58.928 --> 03:00.388
You can barely
keep your eyes open.

03:00.471 --> 03:02.849
- I could sleep forever,
I think.

03:02.932 --> 03:05.184
- Hello.
Wayne residence.

03:05.268 --> 03:08.104
Of course.
I'll fetch him for you.

03:08.187 --> 03:10.732
Phone call for Mr. Pennyworth.

03:10.815 --> 03:13.610
[mysterious tone]

03:16.195 --> 03:18.615
- This is Alfred.
- Alfie.

03:18.698 --> 03:20.199
Thank goodness I found you.

03:20.283 --> 03:22.201
- No one wants tea, then?
- Thanks, Gladys.

03:22.285 --> 03:24.954
- All right.
Thanks, Mr. C.

03:26.539 --> 03:28.041
- Trouble, son?

03:28.124 --> 03:29.667
- That was Chadley.

03:29.751 --> 03:32.378
Lucius in a spot of bother.

03:32.462 --> 03:34.130
- Uh, Mrs. P, would you--

03:34.213 --> 03:35.882
- Yeah.
Come on, Sam.

03:35.965 --> 03:37.634
Let's go run a bath.

03:37.717 --> 03:39.344
[tense music]

03:39.427 --> 03:41.804
- Lucius said,
"Mayday, mayday. Level 7,"

03:41.888 --> 03:43.139
then got cut off.

03:43.222 --> 03:44.432
- Lucius would only use
the mayday signal

03:44.515 --> 03:45.975
if he was in real danger.

03:46.059 --> 03:49.228
- I'm sorry, what's, um--
what's Level 7?

03:50.939 --> 03:52.982
- It's an underground
Army facility.

03:53.066 --> 03:56.027
Finding new and fiendish ways
to weaponize P-dubs.

03:56.110 --> 03:58.237
Lucius was trying
to gain access.

03:58.321 --> 03:59.530
- Oh, for Christ's sake.

03:59.614 --> 04:01.032
What a bad idea.
Why would he do that?

04:01.115 --> 04:02.617
- Because something bad's
going on down there.

04:02.700 --> 04:03.952
Something evil.

04:04.035 --> 04:05.912
- Like what?
- W--I don't know.

04:05.995 --> 04:08.581
They're trying to make weapons
out of human beings.

04:08.665 --> 04:10.333
- Meaning you don't really know
what's going on.

04:10.416 --> 04:11.876
- That's why Lucius
went down there:

04:11.960 --> 04:13.544
to find out the truth.

04:14.587 --> 04:19.008
And I kind of...
encouraged him a bit, so...

04:19.092 --> 04:20.969
- Oh, Jesus, Martha.

04:23.763 --> 04:26.015
[low rumbling]

04:26.099 --> 04:29.018
[tense music]

04:29.102 --> 04:32.355
♪ ♪

04:32.438 --> 04:35.358
- And you're quite sure
that's what he said.

04:35.441 --> 04:37.193
- Certain, sir.

04:37.276 --> 04:38.653
- Mayday?

04:38.736 --> 04:41.197
How strange.
- Isn't it?

04:41.281 --> 04:42.991
So I'll look into that for you

04:43.074 --> 04:44.909
if you give me permission
to go to Level 7.

04:44.993 --> 04:47.537
- Level 7 is,
as you very well know,

04:47.620 --> 04:49.205
an entirely Army operation.

04:49.288 --> 04:50.707
I have no say in the matter.

04:50.790 --> 04:52.667
Relations between
the government and the Army

04:52.750 --> 04:55.003
are in a fragile state
at the moment.

04:55.086 --> 04:56.587
Hostile, in fact.

04:56.671 --> 04:58.256
Extremely hostile.

04:58.339 --> 05:00.008
- Sir, Lucius is being held
against his will

05:00.091 --> 05:02.593
because he knows the truth
about Level 7,

05:02.677 --> 05:04.887
and I fear for his life.
- Possibly true,

05:04.971 --> 05:06.806
but we don't know it
to be true.

05:06.889 --> 05:08.725
I can't act on possibility.
- B-but--

05:08.808 --> 05:13.146
- However, if some
independent entity or person,

05:13.229 --> 05:15.732
without my knowledge
or consent,

05:15.815 --> 05:18.568
were to establish the facts
and found, by whatever means,

05:18.651 --> 05:21.696
that there were crimes
going on down there,

05:21.779 --> 05:23.531
then the police
and the high courts

05:23.614 --> 05:26.993
would take the lead,
not this office.

05:28.119 --> 05:30.246
Which would not make me
unhappy.

05:31.414 --> 05:32.749
- Got it.

05:32.832 --> 05:35.918
Have I got it?
- [sighs] I do hope so.

05:38.212 --> 05:39.589
[bell dings]

05:39.672 --> 05:42.633
[adventurous music]

05:42.717 --> 05:45.261
♪ ♪

05:45.344 --> 05:46.971
Mmm.

05:47.055 --> 05:54.145
♪ ♪

06:15.416 --> 06:22.507
♪ ♪

06:40.483 --> 06:42.902
- He's given us
the green light.

06:42.985 --> 06:44.654
- Th-the green light?

06:44.737 --> 06:46.531
- To go get Lucius.

06:46.614 --> 06:48.574
- What do you mean?
There's nothing we can do.

06:48.658 --> 06:50.326
I mean, w-we can get him
a lawyer, but--

06:50.409 --> 06:53.037
- The prime minister has just
given us tacit permission

06:53.121 --> 06:54.163
to go in and rescue him.

06:54.247 --> 06:56.374
- Rescue him? How?

06:56.457 --> 06:57.792
- However we can.

06:57.875 --> 06:59.585
I have a security pass
for Level 6,

06:59.669 --> 07:01.671
so from there, I'm sure we can
find a way down to Level 7.

07:01.754 --> 07:03.005
- I can't believe
I'm hearing this.

07:03.089 --> 07:04.173
We have just rescued
our daughter

07:04.257 --> 07:06.509
from the clutches of a maniac.

07:06.592 --> 07:09.178
That's enough drama
for one week, don't you think?

07:09.262 --> 07:10.721
- I'm with him.

07:10.805 --> 07:12.932
- Lucius is a friend in danger.

07:13.015 --> 07:15.017
I have to do this, Thomas.
- Martha--

07:15.101 --> 07:16.727
- And they're hiding
something awful down there.

07:16.811 --> 07:18.146
- That's none of our business.

07:18.229 --> 07:19.856
- Well, it is my business!

07:19.939 --> 07:22.233
Those poor souls are my
business because it's my job!

07:22.316 --> 07:23.985
- Yes, yes,
you're a secret agent,

07:24.068 --> 07:26.696
but you're also a wife
and a mother.

07:26.779 --> 07:28.156
And you're part of a family,

07:28.239 --> 07:34.245
a family that's just been
through a serious trauma.

07:34.328 --> 07:36.581
- Well, I'm also a friend
to Lucius.

07:36.664 --> 07:38.374
And you'll be here
to look after Sam.

07:40.293 --> 07:42.128
So...

07:42.211 --> 07:44.255
also, I don't know
what else I can do.

07:46.549 --> 07:47.842
- Fine. Fuck this.

07:47.925 --> 07:50.136
Go be a--
go be a secret fucking agent.

07:53.890 --> 07:55.308
[door closes]

07:56.976 --> 07:58.477
- Please wait. Thomas!

07:58.561 --> 08:01.189
- [sighs]
- Thomas. I'm sorry.

08:02.982 --> 08:04.317
- Sorry about what?

08:04.400 --> 08:06.485
- I am who I am, Thomas.

08:08.154 --> 08:09.322
- Yeah.

08:09.405 --> 08:11.657
You're a little crazy.
- [laughs] Yeah.

08:11.741 --> 08:13.993
But, honey, look who's talking.

08:17.997 --> 08:21.250
- I just wanna go back
to being a normal family.

08:21.334 --> 08:22.960
- Well,
maybe that's not possible.

08:23.044 --> 08:25.922
Maybe we should accept
that we're not normal.

08:26.005 --> 08:28.633
Accept that we're
a strange, fucked-up family.

08:28.716 --> 08:30.593
Just embrace the fuckery.

08:30.676 --> 08:31.969
- No. No.

08:32.053 --> 08:34.138
I vote on going back
to being a normal family.

08:34.222 --> 08:37.767
- You mean stand by and do
nothing when we could help?

08:37.850 --> 08:39.852
- Is it really such a bad idea?

08:39.936 --> 08:41.562
Just this once?

08:47.026 --> 08:48.694
No.

08:48.778 --> 08:50.029
No.

08:50.112 --> 08:51.322
You're gonna go ahead

08:51.405 --> 08:52.949
and "do the right thing,"
aren't you?

08:53.032 --> 08:55.409
- Lucius is in trouble
because of me.

08:55.493 --> 08:57.995
I have to go.
You know that.

08:59.038 --> 09:00.456
Come inside.

09:00.539 --> 09:02.959
[soft suspenseful music]

09:03.042 --> 09:04.460
♪ ♪

09:04.543 --> 09:06.045
Please?

09:06.128 --> 09:13.219
♪ ♪

09:16.555 --> 09:18.724
I'll pay you.

09:18.808 --> 09:20.434
- Excuse me?
- I'll pay you.

09:20.518 --> 09:22.186
To help me go get Lucius.

09:23.354 --> 09:26.691
- Don't look at me.
I would love to come along,

09:26.774 --> 09:28.776
but I--I need a nap.

09:28.859 --> 09:33.614
And Sam needs
at least one sane, live parent.

09:33.698 --> 09:36.325
- I need you, Alfie.
Name your price.

09:36.409 --> 09:38.661
- Well, now you're just trying
to make me feel bad.

09:38.744 --> 09:39.704
- No.

09:39.787 --> 09:41.539
I gave that up a long time ago.

09:41.622 --> 09:42.957
You're unshameable.

09:43.040 --> 09:46.502
♪ ♪

09:46.586 --> 09:48.296
- Call it a tenner.

09:48.379 --> 09:51.424
I'm not doing nothing for free.
I'm not a mug.

09:51.507 --> 09:53.509
Lot of help you were.

09:53.592 --> 09:56.012
- Well, embrace the fuckery,
Alfie.

09:57.972 --> 09:59.682
- Francis!

09:59.765 --> 10:01.100
Oh, thank God we found you.

10:01.183 --> 10:02.351
- Hello, Sally.

10:02.435 --> 10:03.978
- That drug you gave out
to the party,

10:04.061 --> 10:05.771
you have to stop giving it out.

10:05.855 --> 10:07.982
You have to stop right now.
- Stop it?

10:08.065 --> 10:10.026
Nobody can stop it, darling.

10:10.109 --> 10:12.069
Half of London
just had Lullaby milk

10:12.153 --> 10:14.071
in their morning tea.

10:14.155 --> 10:15.531
- Tell us you're joking.

10:15.615 --> 10:17.199
- After you left the party,
people went mad.

10:17.283 --> 10:19.702
- Aye, they killed
yon Dr. Glubb.

10:19.785 --> 10:21.996
- Really?
How?

10:22.079 --> 10:23.748
- What does it matter?

10:23.831 --> 10:25.875
Your drug is fucked!

10:25.958 --> 10:29.378
- Lullaby frees
the inner soul, Daveboy.

10:29.462 --> 10:31.839
Some souls are governed
by love,

10:31.922 --> 10:33.215
others by fear.

10:33.299 --> 10:35.885
Everybody does their own thing.

10:36.635 --> 10:38.929
That's life.
- Death, actually.

10:39.013 --> 10:40.598
- Death is life.

10:40.681 --> 10:42.975
Life is death.

10:43.059 --> 10:45.895
It's wonderful... and horrible

10:45.978 --> 10:49.398
and very, very now.

10:50.649 --> 10:52.568
- It's madness, is what it is.

10:52.651 --> 10:54.695
- You can call it madness
if you wish, Daveboy.

10:54.779 --> 10:56.238
I like to call it joy.

10:56.322 --> 10:57.990
- Francis!

10:58.074 --> 10:59.450
- Aye?

10:59.533 --> 11:01.660
♪ ♪

11:01.744 --> 11:03.537
And what do you call that?

11:03.621 --> 11:05.915
- Don't be scared.
- No?

11:05.998 --> 11:07.625
♪ ♪

11:07.708 --> 11:09.502
- These are my disciples.

11:09.585 --> 11:11.670
[crowd shouting]

11:11.754 --> 11:14.215
My beautiful children!

11:15.633 --> 11:17.843
Give me your love!

11:17.927 --> 11:20.596
[tense music]

11:20.679 --> 11:22.598
♪ ♪

11:22.681 --> 11:24.809
[grunting]

11:24.892 --> 11:26.519
Stop! Stop!

11:26.602 --> 11:28.104
- Go, go, go, go.

11:28.187 --> 11:29.480
Go! Go!

11:29.563 --> 11:36.654
♪ ♪

11:40.533 --> 11:41.826
- Morning.

11:41.909 --> 11:43.619
New intake for Level 6.

11:44.495 --> 11:46.205
Oh, and do you have access
to Level 7?

11:46.288 --> 11:48.707
- Yeah, but you--
- Great. That's good to know.

11:50.376 --> 11:52.420
- Hello, Ms. Kane.
- Hi, Henry.

11:52.503 --> 11:53.754
Sorry about this.

11:53.838 --> 11:56.090
[soldier grunts]
- Sorry about what?

11:57.133 --> 11:59.218
- Get in.
[scanner beeps]

12:00.553 --> 12:01.721
- [grunts]

12:06.142 --> 12:07.935
- Oh.

12:08.894 --> 12:10.604
- Level 7 access granted.

12:10.688 --> 12:14.733
Mind the closing doors.
[elevator dings]

12:14.817 --> 12:17.361
[tense music]

12:17.445 --> 12:19.447
♪ ♪

12:19.530 --> 12:22.575
- You know this
is very sketchy, Alfie.

12:22.658 --> 12:24.285
- I do.

12:24.368 --> 12:26.162
- Thank you for coming.

12:26.245 --> 12:27.913
- There's no need to thank me.

12:27.997 --> 12:29.707
There's a tenner in it.

12:29.790 --> 12:36.881
♪ ♪

12:40.009 --> 12:42.511
- Morning. Ministry inspection.

12:42.595 --> 12:45.222
Take us to General Thursday.

12:45.306 --> 12:46.891
- This way, ma'am.

12:46.974 --> 12:54.064
♪ ♪

12:56.567 --> 12:59.195
- Mrs. Wayne?
Pennyworth?

12:59.278 --> 13:01.322
What the devil
are you doing down here?

13:01.405 --> 13:03.866
You don't have clearance.
- Good day to you, General.

13:03.949 --> 13:05.993
You're holding Lucius Fox here,
I believe.

13:06.076 --> 13:07.745
- Who told you that?
- He did.

13:07.828 --> 13:09.038
- Nonsense.

13:09.121 --> 13:11.624
- We need to see him.
- Oh, really?

13:11.707 --> 13:13.292
On whose authority?

13:13.375 --> 13:14.877
The prime minister
has no right--

13:14.960 --> 13:17.004
- The prime minister
has nothing to do with this.

13:17.087 --> 13:19.340
We're here as private citizens,

13:19.423 --> 13:21.050
representatives of the people.

13:21.133 --> 13:23.511
- The people?
Nonsense.

13:23.594 --> 13:26.555
Aziz sent you.
- Think what you like.

13:26.639 --> 13:29.475
But you're holding Lucius Fox
without charges or a warrant,

13:29.558 --> 13:32.228
and I am here exercising
his habeas corpus rights.

13:32.311 --> 13:33.729
- [laughs]

13:33.812 --> 13:35.648
Civilian jargon.

13:35.731 --> 13:38.067
You're trespassers
in a high-security,

13:38.150 --> 13:40.277
high-value military facility

13:40.361 --> 13:43.572
guarded
by a battalion of soldiers.

13:44.532 --> 13:46.075
- Really?
- Hmm.

13:46.158 --> 13:48.702
- 'Cause the way I see it,
we're in a little room

13:48.786 --> 13:50.204
just the three of us.

13:50.287 --> 13:52.081
- Five of us, actually.

13:54.208 --> 13:55.376
[all grunting]

13:55.459 --> 13:57.253
- What the hell?

13:59.880 --> 14:02.800
[tense music]

14:02.883 --> 14:03.926
- Three.

14:04.009 --> 14:05.678
- You just committed treason.

14:05.761 --> 14:07.012
- Get on that PA system

14:07.096 --> 14:09.473
and tell your soldiers
to stand down.

14:09.557 --> 14:12.101
- What are you going to do,
shoot me?

14:12.184 --> 14:13.477
- That's right.
- [chuckles]

14:13.561 --> 14:15.062
- [chuckles]
- She's bluffing.

14:15.145 --> 14:16.605
- I wouldn't bet on that, mate.

14:16.689 --> 14:18.107
- I won't kill you.

14:18.190 --> 14:20.067
I'll just wound you.

14:21.068 --> 14:22.945
- You're crazy.
- Hmm.

14:23.028 --> 14:24.738
I'm beginning
to understand that.

14:24.822 --> 14:26.448
It's very liberating, actually.

14:26.532 --> 14:30.286
- I'm the commander in chief
of the bloody Army.

14:30.369 --> 14:31.787
You can't do this.

14:31.870 --> 14:33.289
- Well, you wouldn't think so,
would you?

14:33.372 --> 14:34.582
But here we are.

14:34.665 --> 14:36.250
And you don't mind me saying,
sir,

14:36.333 --> 14:38.377
you don't run
a very tight ship.

14:38.460 --> 14:43.090
♪ ♪

14:43.173 --> 14:44.633
[feedback over PA]
- Get off!

14:44.717 --> 14:46.385
- Attention all personnel,

14:46.468 --> 14:49.847
this is your commander
in chief, General Thursday.

14:49.930 --> 14:54.143
This facility is now under
civilian control.

14:54.226 --> 14:56.270
[soft acoustic music]

14:56.353 --> 14:59.648
I repeat,
under civilian control.

14:59.732 --> 15:01.609
Stand down from your duties

15:01.692 --> 15:04.403
and stow
your weapons immediately.

15:04.486 --> 15:07.156
- ♪ We are as birds ♪

15:07.239 --> 15:11.535
♪ Fluttering
in momentary light ♪

15:11.619 --> 15:13.662
♪ ♪

15:13.746 --> 15:16.498
♪ Before we return again ♪

15:16.582 --> 15:20.711
♪ To the blackness
of the night ♪

15:20.794 --> 15:24.548
♪ ♪

15:24.632 --> 15:25.758
[door opens]

15:25.841 --> 15:27.509
- Sir, we have an ongoing

15:27.593 --> 15:30.137
mental health emergency
across the city.

15:30.220 --> 15:31.347
- Oh.

15:31.430 --> 15:32.806
- People are going mad,

15:32.890 --> 15:34.850
and nobody knows
what's causing it.

15:34.933 --> 15:36.852
Some have turned violent.

15:36.935 --> 15:38.562
They're forming mobs.

15:38.646 --> 15:40.314
[tense music]
[horse neighs]

15:40.397 --> 15:42.191
- Mobs, you say?

15:42.274 --> 15:45.861
♪ ♪

15:45.944 --> 15:48.197
What do they want?
- They're mad, sir.

15:48.280 --> 15:51.408
They don't want anything.
- Nonsense.

15:52.701 --> 15:54.411
Everybody wants something.

15:54.495 --> 15:57.498
♪ ♪

15:57.581 --> 15:59.375
Secure the gates.

15:59.458 --> 16:01.710
Call out the guards.

16:02.878 --> 16:05.130
Let no one enter.
- Yes, sir.

16:05.214 --> 16:06.215
- Mm.

16:07.341 --> 16:11.261
- An unknown entity is causing
widespread, mass psychosis

16:11.345 --> 16:13.430
throughout central London.

16:13.514 --> 16:16.600
Police and ambulance services
have been suspended--

16:16.684 --> 16:18.060
- [person shouts]
- Ahh!

16:18.143 --> 16:19.520
- Die!

16:19.603 --> 16:21.313
[Labi Siffre's
"It Must Be Love" playing]

16:21.397 --> 16:23.273
- ♪ As soon as I wake up ♪

16:23.357 --> 16:26.193
♪ Any night, any day ♪

16:26.276 --> 16:27.569
♪ ♪

16:27.653 --> 16:29.905
♪ I know
that it's you I need ♪

16:29.988 --> 16:32.574
♪ To take the blues away ♪

16:32.658 --> 16:33.951
♪ ♪

16:34.034 --> 16:35.244
♪ It must be love ♪

16:35.327 --> 16:37.579
- Oh! Listen to me,
all of you.

16:38.872 --> 16:40.082
Listen!

16:40.165 --> 16:42.084
There are nutters coming here.

16:42.167 --> 16:43.460
We need to secure
this building.

16:43.544 --> 16:45.504
Chadley, open up the gun safe.

16:45.587 --> 16:49.091
You and you, come with me.

16:49.174 --> 16:50.426
Jesus.

16:50.509 --> 16:53.095
- He's not joking. Seriously.

16:53.178 --> 16:55.264
♪ ♪

16:55.347 --> 16:57.057
[chainsaw buzzes]

16:57.141 --> 16:59.143
- Fuck.

16:59.226 --> 17:00.811
Ahh!

17:00.894 --> 17:02.896
Move! Come on!

17:02.980 --> 17:04.314
- Righto.

17:04.398 --> 17:06.650
- ♪ Nothing more,
nothing less ♪

17:06.734 --> 17:08.652
♪ Love is the best ♪

17:08.736 --> 17:10.279
- Thank God.

17:10.362 --> 17:11.864
Thank you.

17:11.947 --> 17:13.490
I'm impressed.

17:13.574 --> 17:15.075
Thank you.
- No problem.

17:15.159 --> 17:17.369
Are you okay?
- I'm okay.

17:17.453 --> 17:19.079
A little traumatized,
I suspect, but--

17:19.163 --> 17:20.456
- Time to go, eh?

17:20.539 --> 17:22.166
- We can't go yet.

17:23.333 --> 17:25.461
...3-4-8.
[panel beeps]

17:25.544 --> 17:26.378
- Come on!

17:26.462 --> 17:28.338
- Whoa!
- Oh.

17:28.422 --> 17:30.174
Sorry.
- Bet.

17:30.257 --> 17:31.675
- Alfie?

17:31.759 --> 17:33.051
- Hello. Ow!

17:33.135 --> 17:35.971
What the fuck? Careful.
- Sorry.

17:36.054 --> 17:38.307
Mrs. Wayne. Well, I never.

17:38.390 --> 17:39.641
- What are you doing here?

17:39.725 --> 17:41.852
- You may well ask.
Long story.

17:41.935 --> 17:43.520
I found John Salt, and then--
- For later.

17:43.604 --> 17:46.106
We need to go.
- We can't go yet.

17:47.274 --> 17:48.817
- What now?

17:48.901 --> 17:50.778
[beeping]
- Okay, guys.

17:51.779 --> 17:53.822
They need to come with us.
- No.

17:53.906 --> 17:55.324
- We can't just leave them
in here.

17:55.407 --> 17:56.533
This is a torture chamber.

17:56.617 --> 17:58.285
- Where are you gonna take 'em?

17:58.368 --> 18:00.621
- We'll worry about that when
we've got them out of here.

18:00.704 --> 18:01.830
- Yeah, but come on--
- No, he's right.

18:01.914 --> 18:03.248
They can't stay here.

18:03.332 --> 18:06.585
- What's going on, Lucius?
- Guys, listen.

18:06.668 --> 18:08.128
We're gonna get you
out of here.

18:08.212 --> 18:09.797
[cheers and applause]
[cell door bangs]

18:09.880 --> 18:11.799
So this gadget...

18:11.882 --> 18:13.634
will open the lock
in two hours.

18:13.717 --> 18:15.886
If you mess with it, the doors
won't open at all.

18:15.969 --> 18:17.346
Ever. Okay?

18:17.429 --> 18:18.806
So don't mess with it.

18:18.889 --> 18:20.390
[timer buzzes]

18:22.726 --> 18:24.144
[timer beeping]

18:24.228 --> 18:25.896
Oh, and don't try
breaking through the walls

18:25.979 --> 18:27.397
because that, as you know,

18:27.481 --> 18:29.566
would trigger
those self-destruct protocols

18:29.650 --> 18:30.901
that you insisted on.

18:30.984 --> 18:33.487
- Tell Aziz
he'll hang for this.

18:33.570 --> 18:34.905
- May I finish explaining
the situation?

18:34.988 --> 18:36.907
- You'll hang too!
Mark my words.

18:36.990 --> 18:38.575
- Once you get out
of this cage,

18:38.659 --> 18:40.452
you'll have full use
of the amenities on this floor,

18:40.536 --> 18:42.371
but you'll find that you're
unable to get to the surface

18:42.454 --> 18:45.040
because I'll have cut the power
to the lifts and air locks.

18:45.124 --> 18:47.125
- All of you will hang
for this.

18:47.209 --> 18:48.919
- You'll be free to go
once your ex-inmates

18:49.002 --> 18:50.546
are safely out of your reach.

18:50.629 --> 18:52.089
I'd estimate a couple of days.

18:52.172 --> 18:55.217
Uh, yeah.
I think that's it.

18:55.300 --> 18:57.970
Good luck,
and God be with you, sir.

18:58.053 --> 19:00.806
[dramatic music]

19:00.889 --> 19:04.101
♪ ♪

19:04.184 --> 19:05.811
- Oh, that's not good.

19:05.894 --> 19:08.355
[people shouting]

19:08.438 --> 19:11.316
- What the heck is going on?

19:12.359 --> 19:15.696
- Uh, wild guess: Lullaby.
- Fuck.

19:15.779 --> 19:17.948
- I mean, it must be
in the water or something.

19:18.031 --> 19:19.241
- What's Lullaby?

19:19.324 --> 19:21.368
[machine gun firing]

19:21.451 --> 19:23.954
- Whoo!
[radio playing loudly]

19:24.037 --> 19:25.539
- That's Lullaby.

19:25.622 --> 19:28.417
♪ ♪

19:28.500 --> 19:30.294
- I hate that fucking song.

19:30.377 --> 19:34.798
What's it even mean,
caravans and candlesticks?

19:34.882 --> 19:36.967
- Oh, no. Sandra.

19:37.050 --> 19:38.176
Listen,
you get to the Queen Anne

19:38.260 --> 19:39.595
and I'll see you there!

19:39.678 --> 19:41.013
- Oh, fuck.
Sam. Thomas.

19:41.096 --> 19:43.140
Get to the Queen Anne!
- Hey, wh--

19:44.182 --> 19:46.727
- Oh, for God's sake.
- Okay, come on.

19:46.810 --> 19:49.104
[people shouting]

19:49.187 --> 19:52.024
[crowd chattering]

19:54.526 --> 19:55.819
- Guys.

19:55.903 --> 19:58.155
Guys!
[chattering unintelligibly]

19:58.238 --> 20:00.282
Listen!
[crowd quiets]

20:00.365 --> 20:02.576
Thank you.
[chattering continues]

20:02.659 --> 20:05.787
So look, we have a dangerous
situation out there.

20:05.871 --> 20:07.164
- Quiet!

20:07.247 --> 20:08.790
[crowd quiets]

20:08.874 --> 20:11.043
Let the man speak.

20:11.126 --> 20:13.337
- Thank you. Yes.

20:13.420 --> 20:16.173
A dangerous situation.
[machine gun fire in distance]

20:16.256 --> 20:17.633
We're gonna be okay.

20:17.716 --> 20:19.968
- Sandra!
[crowd shouting]

20:20.052 --> 20:22.471
- Sandra!

20:22.554 --> 20:25.307
- Come down, Sandra!

20:25.390 --> 20:28.185
- Sandra!
- We love you!

20:28.268 --> 20:30.145
- Come down here, Sandra!

20:30.228 --> 20:32.731
[soft acoustic music]

20:32.814 --> 20:35.233
- ♪ Dull and dreary day ♪

20:35.317 --> 20:37.235
♪ Sad and gloomy gray ♪

20:37.319 --> 20:39.237
♪ The cold wind blew
the northside ♪

20:39.321 --> 20:42.824
♪ On the rooftop weathervane ♪

20:42.908 --> 20:45.410
♪ The sky was overcast ♪

20:45.494 --> 20:47.162
♪ Moving mighty fast ♪

20:47.245 --> 20:51.792
♪ And at the very moment
I expected pouring rain ♪

20:51.875 --> 20:53.877
♪ ♪

20:53.961 --> 20:55.420
- Come on.

20:55.504 --> 20:58.674
♪ ♪

20:58.757 --> 21:00.175
- Are you mad?

21:00.259 --> 21:01.468
- Sorry to scare you.

21:01.551 --> 21:02.803
I had to come over the roof.
- Why?

21:02.886 --> 21:04.262
- We need
to get out of here now.

21:04.346 --> 21:05.764
- Fuck off. I'm not
going anywhere with you.

21:05.847 --> 21:07.766
- Listen. Can you hear that?
[people shouting]

21:07.849 --> 21:09.142
- Yes. So what?

21:09.226 --> 21:10.852
I get that all the time.
Fans are crazy.

21:10.936 --> 21:12.521
- Yeah, but these fans
have been given the same drug

21:12.604 --> 21:14.022
they gave Jessica Thistle.

21:14.106 --> 21:15.816
They've gone mad,
and they're coming for you.

21:15.899 --> 21:17.150
Now.
- For me?

21:17.234 --> 21:18.694
Why?
- Well, I don't know.

21:18.777 --> 21:20.237
But they don't want
your fucking autograph.

21:20.320 --> 21:22.322
- You're taking the piss.
- Why would I do that?

21:22.406 --> 21:23.907
- I don't know.
I don't know.

21:23.991 --> 21:25.450
Honestly, I don't know
what goes on in your head.

21:25.534 --> 21:27.327
Sometimes I think
you must really hate me.

21:27.411 --> 21:29.371
- Oh, give over.
You know I don't.

21:29.454 --> 21:30.539
I love you.

21:30.622 --> 21:32.958
- [scoffs] Bollocks. Bollocks.

21:33.041 --> 21:34.543
That's just a silly word
to you.

21:34.626 --> 21:35.961
You don't know what love is.

21:36.044 --> 21:38.255
I know
because I used to love you.

21:38.338 --> 21:40.549
Used to. Now I hate you.

21:40.632 --> 21:42.843
Seriously.
Quite a lot, actually.

21:42.926 --> 21:44.886
And I'm not going anywhere
with you, thank you very much.

21:44.970 --> 21:47.472
- Look, I don't blame you.
I've been a right bastard.

21:47.556 --> 21:48.932
- Sandra!

21:49.016 --> 21:50.642
- We love you, Sandra!

21:53.854 --> 21:56.231
- Uh, sorry. Yeah.

21:56.314 --> 21:57.691
Listen.

21:57.774 --> 21:59.192
I've been a right bastard,

21:59.276 --> 22:01.069
but I'll make it up to you.

22:01.153 --> 22:03.405
- One, two three...
- Oh, please!

22:03.488 --> 22:05.532
- Four, five, six.

22:05.615 --> 22:06.742
Another throw.

22:06.825 --> 22:08.952
- Ahh! Ahh.

22:09.036 --> 22:10.871
- Yay, five! A ladder.

22:10.954 --> 22:13.582
[tense music]
[people shouting outside]

22:14.499 --> 22:17.127
Your go, Daddy.
[Gladys whimpers]

22:17.210 --> 22:18.462
[door shuts]

22:19.629 --> 22:21.757
Mummy!
- Oh!

22:21.840 --> 22:22.966
Hey, guys.

22:23.050 --> 22:25.177
- Oh, thank goodness
you're all right.

22:25.260 --> 22:27.346
- So, um...

22:27.429 --> 22:28.847
how did it go?

22:28.930 --> 22:30.599
- Yes. Good. Yes.

22:30.682 --> 22:32.350
Yeah. We got Lucius out,
no problem.

22:32.434 --> 22:35.228
- Good, um...
[Gladys whimpers]

22:35.312 --> 22:37.856
- The tea's rea--ready!

22:37.939 --> 22:39.107
[mutters]

22:39.191 --> 22:40.400
- Uh...

22:40.484 --> 22:42.444
Well, I guess
I'm just wondering what--

22:42.527 --> 22:43.945
- Oh, yeah, what?

22:44.029 --> 22:45.489
That half the city's
gone insane? Yeah.

22:45.572 --> 22:46.948
Yeah, we noticed that.

22:47.032 --> 22:49.284
- Gladys tried
to set the kitchen on fire.

22:49.367 --> 22:50.368
- She did?

22:50.452 --> 22:52.287
Mrs. P had to sit on her.

22:52.370 --> 22:53.663
- Oh, God.

22:53.747 --> 22:55.040
- Yeah, it was quite the drama.

22:55.123 --> 22:56.291
- [whimpers]

22:56.375 --> 22:57.876
- Um, can we--

22:57.959 --> 22:59.294
- Yes.

23:00.420 --> 23:01.755
- Your go, Mrs. P.

23:01.838 --> 23:03.006
- Those afflicted appear

23:03.090 --> 23:04.508
to be in their own
little world,

23:04.591 --> 23:06.051
with a great deal
of violent presentation.

23:06.134 --> 23:08.512
- Yep. Pretty safe bet
it's Lullaby related.

23:08.595 --> 23:10.222
- Yeah.
- I mean, ironically enough,

23:10.305 --> 23:11.640
this is also
your father's fault.

23:11.723 --> 23:13.391
- I'm not sure that's
the correct use

23:13.475 --> 23:16.394
of "ironically," but yes,
the Wayne family strikes again.

23:17.354 --> 23:20.482
So I suppose now we're
responsible to save London.

23:20.565 --> 23:22.400
- I guess
if we could save London,

23:22.484 --> 23:23.819
it would be our responsibility.

23:23.902 --> 23:25.028
But we can't.

23:25.112 --> 23:26.530
At least,
I can't think of anything.

23:26.613 --> 23:28.323
Can you?
- No.

23:28.406 --> 23:30.325
- Kay, well, I vote
we get the hell out of town

23:30.408 --> 23:32.828
for a couple of days
at the seaside.

23:32.911 --> 23:34.287
- Hallelujah.

23:34.371 --> 23:36.039
A normal person
sensible response.

23:36.123 --> 23:37.582
Thank you.
- You're welcome.

23:37.666 --> 23:40.585
Just one question:
how do we do that?

23:40.669 --> 23:42.838
Get outta town?

23:42.921 --> 23:44.923
- I-I have no idea.

23:46.133 --> 23:48.718
- [laughs]

23:50.512 --> 23:51.930
Are we good now?

23:53.473 --> 23:55.016
I mean, you and me?

23:55.100 --> 23:56.852
- You mean am I willing
and able to live with a woman

23:56.935 --> 23:59.479
who thinks
she's a comic book detective?

23:59.563 --> 24:00.939
- Mm, yeah.

24:01.022 --> 24:03.024
I guess that's what I mean.

24:03.108 --> 24:04.860
[dramatic music]

24:04.943 --> 24:07.237
- Yes.
I love you.

24:07.320 --> 24:08.780
I don't know why,
but I love you,

24:08.864 --> 24:11.783
so the answer is--it's...

24:11.867 --> 24:13.076
yes.

24:14.452 --> 24:17.330
The question is,
can a desperado like you

24:17.414 --> 24:19.541
live with a man
who wants peace and quiet

24:19.624 --> 24:21.293
and a simple family life?

24:21.376 --> 24:22.836
- No.

24:24.129 --> 24:25.547
I'm kidding. [laughs]

24:25.630 --> 24:27.048
I'm kidding. Yes.
- Oh.

24:27.132 --> 24:28.550
- Yes, I can.

24:28.633 --> 24:29.801
With all my heart.

24:29.885 --> 24:36.975
♪ ♪

24:39.019 --> 24:41.229
[clattering]

24:41.313 --> 24:44.232
[unintelligible chatter]

24:44.316 --> 24:47.235
[tense music]

24:47.319 --> 24:53.783
♪ ♪

24:53.867 --> 24:56.203
- I hear people coming.

24:57.746 --> 25:00.248
♪ ♪

25:00.332 --> 25:02.250
Oh, dear.

25:02.334 --> 25:03.543
- Steady.

25:03.627 --> 25:05.629
- Easy for you to say.

25:05.712 --> 25:07.839
Killing people
is your occupation.

25:07.923 --> 25:12.427
♪ ♪

25:12.510 --> 25:13.595
[cocks gun]

25:13.678 --> 25:16.598
[dramatic music]

25:16.681 --> 25:20.143
♪ ♪

25:20.227 --> 25:22.187
Oh, my gosh!

25:23.730 --> 25:25.899
- What the fuck?

25:25.982 --> 25:33.073
♪ ♪

25:36.368 --> 25:38.745
- [panting] Hello, lads.

25:43.208 --> 25:46.586
- All clear. Ready?

25:46.670 --> 25:48.046
[glass shatters]

25:48.129 --> 25:49.923
- Why do we have
to go out there?

25:50.006 --> 25:51.341
Couldn't we just hide
in here somewhere?

25:51.424 --> 25:52.592
- No, they're all over
the building.

25:52.676 --> 25:53.843
We can't risk it.

25:53.927 --> 25:54.970
But the car's
just down the road.

25:55.053 --> 25:56.513
You'll be fine.

25:56.596 --> 25:57.931
- I don't want to go out there.

25:58.014 --> 25:59.432
- Trust me.
You're safe as houses.

25:59.516 --> 26:01.309
- I don't trust you.
That's the problem.

26:01.393 --> 26:02.852
You're not trustworthy.
- Yeah, all right.

26:02.936 --> 26:04.312
Fair play, but listen.

26:04.396 --> 26:06.481
With this sort of business,
you can trust me.

26:08.316 --> 26:10.026
Look, I'm not gonna let
any harm come to you

26:10.110 --> 26:11.486
or our child.

26:11.569 --> 26:13.613
Never. I promise.

26:14.572 --> 26:15.824
- All right.

26:15.907 --> 26:17.284
But just 'cause
I'm coming with you now

26:17.367 --> 26:18.576
doesn't mean we're made up.
- Yeah.

26:18.660 --> 26:19.828
- Or together or anything.

26:19.911 --> 26:21.246
As far as I'm concerned,
we're over.

26:21.329 --> 26:22.622
- Yeah. All right.
Whatever you say.

26:22.706 --> 26:24.332
Now come on.
- Exactly. Thank you.

26:24.416 --> 26:26.793
You've proved my point.
- What point?

26:26.876 --> 26:29.671
- [sighs] "If you say so."

26:29.754 --> 26:32.173
If you did love me,
you'd tell me I'm wrong.

26:32.257 --> 26:33.967
You'd fight me.
- Fight you?

26:34.050 --> 26:35.927
We're escaping
from a mob of nutters.

26:36.011 --> 26:37.762
I can't fight you now.
I'll fight you later.

26:37.846 --> 26:39.347
- Yeah, that's you.

26:39.431 --> 26:40.849
Always avoiding the issue.

26:40.932 --> 26:42.600
Always twisting your way
out of being honest.

26:42.684 --> 26:44.477
- I'm always honest with you.

26:44.561 --> 26:45.812
- Really?

26:47.188 --> 26:48.523
Who was the last woman
you had sex with?

26:48.606 --> 26:50.942
- Oh, leave off.
- See?

26:51.026 --> 26:52.819
Not me then.

26:54.863 --> 26:56.531
Who was the little slut?

26:56.614 --> 26:57.866
Did you love her too?

26:57.949 --> 26:59.367
- What's that got to do
with anything?

26:59.451 --> 27:01.119
- Just be honest, Alfie.

27:04.831 --> 27:08.126
I'm not moving until I hear
something honest.

27:11.838 --> 27:13.882
- Her name was Zara.

27:13.965 --> 27:15.842
She was a client, all right?

27:15.925 --> 27:17.552
You happy now?

27:17.635 --> 27:18.720
- Zara?

27:18.803 --> 27:20.347
[people shouting in distance]

27:20.430 --> 27:22.390
Foreign, was she?

27:22.474 --> 27:23.808
What'd she look like?

27:23.892 --> 27:25.769
- Well, she--
[people shouting]

27:25.852 --> 27:27.771
- Sandra! Sandra!

27:27.854 --> 27:29.564
Sandra!
- Sandra!

27:29.647 --> 27:31.024
- Sandra!
- Sandra!

27:31.107 --> 27:33.026
[dramatic music]

27:33.109 --> 27:35.070
[person screams]
- Sandra!

27:35.153 --> 27:36.529
Sandra!
- Sandra!

27:36.613 --> 27:38.865
- Get down here!

27:39.991 --> 27:41.451
- Sandra!

27:41.534 --> 27:42.786
Sandra!

27:42.869 --> 27:45.580
♪ ♪

27:45.663 --> 27:46.998
- Come on!

27:47.082 --> 27:54.172
♪ ♪

28:03.098 --> 28:04.307
- Gentlemen.

28:04.391 --> 28:05.725
- Cheers, Mr. C.

28:05.809 --> 28:07.602
- You're very welcome.

28:09.813 --> 28:11.106
[engine roars]

28:11.189 --> 28:13.108
- Aye-aye.
- Who's this, then?

28:13.191 --> 28:14.234
- It's all right.
It's a friend.

28:14.317 --> 28:17.237
[tense music]

28:17.320 --> 28:18.446
♪ ♪

28:18.530 --> 28:20.448
- Come on.
Hello, chaps.

28:20.532 --> 28:21.658
- All right.

28:21.741 --> 28:24.077
- Get ready.
Nutters on our tail.

28:24.160 --> 28:25.870
Oh, Sandra, this is, um...

28:25.954 --> 28:27.414
- Kevin.

28:27.497 --> 28:29.374
It's so nice to meet you,
Sandra.

28:29.457 --> 28:31.209
Big fan.

28:31.292 --> 28:32.544
- Hello.

28:32.627 --> 28:34.295
[people screaming in distance]

28:34.379 --> 28:35.839
- Cheers, Kevin.

28:35.922 --> 28:38.258
See, I told you
it would be safe.

28:38.341 --> 28:39.801
- Thanks for your help.

28:39.884 --> 28:40.969
Send me an invoice.

28:41.052 --> 28:42.720
- Well, don't be like that.

28:43.596 --> 28:45.306
Oh, fine.
Be like that then.

28:45.390 --> 28:47.308
[people shouting]
- Sandra!

28:47.392 --> 28:49.686
- Sandra!
- Sandra!

28:49.769 --> 28:51.146
- Wait, wait, wait, wait.

28:51.229 --> 28:53.314
[guns blasting]

28:53.398 --> 28:55.608
[people shouting]

28:58.236 --> 29:01.030
[timer beeping]

29:01.114 --> 29:02.490
- Come on. Come on!

29:02.574 --> 29:03.658
[beeps]

29:03.741 --> 29:05.201
[rhythmic drum music]

29:05.285 --> 29:07.996
Follow me!

29:09.080 --> 29:10.248
- There's no way up, sir.

29:10.331 --> 29:11.833
The power's cut off,
as Dr. Fox said.

29:11.916 --> 29:13.168
If we tamper with the system,

29:13.251 --> 29:14.919
the self-destruct protocol
kicks in.

29:15.003 --> 29:16.337
- Call the barracks.

29:16.421 --> 29:17.839
Send in a squad topside

29:17.922 --> 29:19.549
to get access
and come down to us.

29:19.632 --> 29:21.009
- Same problem applies, sir.

29:21.092 --> 29:22.719
The self-destruct protocol
will destroy

29:22.802 --> 29:23.887
the whole facility.

29:23.970 --> 29:26.014
- All right.
All right!

29:26.097 --> 29:27.682
Damn Aziz.

29:27.765 --> 29:29.767
[phone beeps]

29:30.810 --> 29:33.771
[tense music]

29:33.855 --> 29:36.024
♪ ♪

29:36.107 --> 29:38.693
Hello? Hello?

29:38.776 --> 29:40.987
Aziz?
- Yes?

29:41.070 --> 29:43.656
- What the devil do you think
you're playing at?

29:43.740 --> 29:46.075
- Who is this?
- Don't play games with me.

29:46.159 --> 29:49.245
You know damn well
this is General Thursday.

29:49.329 --> 29:50.914
- Thursday.

29:50.997 --> 29:52.790
Nobody speaks to me
in that tone.

29:52.874 --> 29:54.417
What's the matter with you?

29:54.501 --> 29:57.879
- Aside from imprisoning me
and my soldiers,

29:57.962 --> 30:02.884
You've released a mob
of incredibly dangerous PWEs

30:02.967 --> 30:04.594
onto the streets of London!

30:04.677 --> 30:07.055
- I haven't the faintest idea
what you're talking about.

30:07.138 --> 30:09.390
- You better get us
out of here pretty damn quick

30:09.474 --> 30:10.892
or there'll be hell to pay!

30:10.975 --> 30:12.101
Do you hear me?

30:12.185 --> 30:14.187
- You threaten me?

30:14.270 --> 30:15.730
Are you drunk?

30:15.813 --> 30:18.483
Don't you know
I can destroy you with a word?

30:19.692 --> 30:21.277
- What do you mean by that?

30:21.361 --> 30:23.571
- You know damn well
what I mean,

30:23.655 --> 30:26.074
you mutinous dog!

30:26.157 --> 30:27.534
[phone chimes]

30:29.244 --> 30:31.371
- My God.
- Sir?

30:32.789 --> 30:34.457
- Aziz wants me gone.

30:34.541 --> 30:36.668
- Easier said than done, sir,
I should say.

30:36.751 --> 30:38.086
- Don't you see?

30:38.169 --> 30:41.589
Aziz and that wretched
scientist are in cahoots.

30:41.673 --> 30:45.426
And that scientist designed
the infrastructure here.

30:45.510 --> 30:47.095
- Yes, sir?

30:47.178 --> 30:50.056
- The self-destruct protocol,
man.

30:50.139 --> 30:53.184
The self-destruct protocol.

30:55.186 --> 30:57.814
We're trapped inside a bomb.

30:57.897 --> 31:01.734
And Aziz can blow us sky high.

31:02.860 --> 31:04.445
[people shouting]

31:04.529 --> 31:06.281
[glass shatters]

31:06.364 --> 31:09.325
- Get Sandra!
- We love you!

31:09.409 --> 31:11.035
- Save him!

31:11.119 --> 31:12.662
[glass shatters]

31:14.372 --> 31:15.665
[hammer clicks]

31:19.085 --> 31:20.545
- Christ.

31:20.628 --> 31:22.422
I hate this.

31:22.505 --> 31:24.549
Just poor souls
off their heads.

31:24.632 --> 31:27.218
- Well, on the bright side,
we'll run out of ammo soon.

31:28.428 --> 31:30.263
- We should send Sandra
out there, eh?

31:30.346 --> 31:32.181
Once they've had their way
with the poor wee hen,

31:32.265 --> 31:34.726
they'll leave us alone, I bet.

31:34.809 --> 31:36.019
- Funny.

31:36.102 --> 31:37.854
- You got a better idea?

31:39.063 --> 31:41.399
[crowd shouting]

31:47.530 --> 31:51.242
[baby whines]

31:51.326 --> 31:52.827
- [softly] Hi.

31:52.910 --> 31:55.872
Yeah?
See your little rattle.

31:55.955 --> 31:58.583
- Well, well, well.

31:59.834 --> 32:01.544
- How you been keeping?

32:01.628 --> 32:03.171
- Not so bad.

32:03.254 --> 32:05.506
You?
- Mustn't grumble.

32:05.590 --> 32:07.216
- How long have you
been sitting there?

32:07.300 --> 32:08.301
- Not long.

32:08.384 --> 32:09.677
- Well, why didn't you wake us?

32:09.761 --> 32:13.723
- It were nice,
watching you sleep.

32:13.806 --> 32:16.100
That peaceful look
on your face.

32:16.184 --> 32:18.519
- Everybody said you were dead.
I knew you were all right.

32:18.603 --> 32:20.938
- More than I did.
- I knew you'd be back.

32:21.022 --> 32:23.691
I knew you wouldn't leave us
to cope with a fucking baby.

32:23.775 --> 32:25.526
- I wouldn't do that to you.

32:25.610 --> 32:27.987
[baby coos]
[chuckles]

32:28.071 --> 32:31.199
Well, fair play, I would,
but I didn't.

32:31.282 --> 32:33.534
So...

32:35.953 --> 32:38.164
She's all right, though,
isn't she?

32:38.247 --> 32:39.874
Hmm?
[baby coos]

32:39.957 --> 32:41.584
- She'll do.

32:41.668 --> 32:43.795
- She's a right smasher.

32:43.878 --> 32:45.546
I could bite you.

32:45.630 --> 32:47.548
I could eat you all up.

32:47.632 --> 32:48.883
[gasps] Boo!

32:48.966 --> 32:52.220
- I won't ask
what you've been at.

32:52.303 --> 32:55.223
- You wouldn't believe us
any road.

32:55.306 --> 32:57.975
I killed John Salt.
[baby coos]

32:58.059 --> 32:59.560
I said I would, and I did.

32:59.644 --> 33:03.439
- So I heard.
I can't approve, but...

33:03.523 --> 33:05.900
well, I'm glad you got it
out of your system at least.

33:05.983 --> 33:08.361
- I've been through the mill,
Peg.

33:08.444 --> 33:09.987
Through the fucking mill.

33:10.071 --> 33:12.240
- You're a magnet for trouble,
eh?

33:12.323 --> 33:13.950
And you don't change.

33:14.033 --> 33:16.160
- I have changed, though, sis.

33:16.244 --> 33:17.537
[baby coos]

33:17.620 --> 33:19.372
They did things to me.

33:19.455 --> 33:22.083
- Men, eh?
Fucking animals.

33:22.166 --> 33:24.919
Let it bother you.
[baby babbles]

33:25.002 --> 33:27.964
[eerie music]

33:28.047 --> 33:30.925
♪ ♪

33:31.008 --> 33:33.177
- Speak.
- Listen.

33:33.261 --> 33:35.555
Before this goes too far,

33:35.638 --> 33:37.765
we should talk.
- I'm listening.

33:37.849 --> 33:40.935
- I gather you think
you have a strong hand.

33:41.018 --> 33:43.062
But please remember, my friend,

33:43.146 --> 33:46.899
I have my own,
very powerful, resources.

33:46.983 --> 33:49.318
- "My friend," he calls me.

33:49.402 --> 33:51.779
I am your sovereign ruler!

33:51.863 --> 33:53.781
Do you not agree?

33:53.865 --> 33:56.367
- You are the lawful head
of the government.

33:56.451 --> 33:58.077
- Yes, I am.

33:58.161 --> 34:00.288
And I will deal with you
as I see fit!

34:00.371 --> 34:03.374
And the people will applaud,
no doubt.

34:05.209 --> 34:07.462
- I'm willing to listen
to your larger concerns

34:07.545 --> 34:09.130
in good faith.

34:09.213 --> 34:11.591
Tell me what you want.

34:11.674 --> 34:13.801
- What do I want?

34:13.885 --> 34:16.804
I want you servile or gone.

34:16.888 --> 34:18.931
I have the power
to get you gone.

34:19.015 --> 34:21.267
Don't test my patience!

34:21.350 --> 34:22.643
[phone chimes]

34:24.729 --> 34:26.814
- This is a coup.

34:26.898 --> 34:29.567
He means to set himself up
as a dictator

34:29.650 --> 34:32.487
and kill us all in the process.

34:32.570 --> 34:35.656
Well, he won't get away
with it.

34:35.740 --> 34:38.409
Patch me through
to bomber command.

34:38.493 --> 34:39.827
- Yes, sir.

34:41.287 --> 34:44.248
[tense music]

34:44.332 --> 34:45.583
♪ ♪

34:45.666 --> 34:47.418
[people shouting]

34:47.502 --> 34:50.463
[piano riff playing]

34:50.546 --> 34:52.965
♪ ♪

34:53.049 --> 34:56.844
- ♪ At first I was afraid,
I was petrified ♪

34:56.928 --> 35:01.140
♪ Kept thinking I could never
life without you by my side ♪

35:01.224 --> 35:03.684
♪ But then I spent
so many nights ♪

35:03.768 --> 35:05.520
♪ Thinking
how you did me wrong ♪

35:05.603 --> 35:07.438
♪ And I grew strong ♪
- Whoo-hoo!

35:07.522 --> 35:09.524
- ♪ And I learned
how to get along ♪

35:09.607 --> 35:11.359
♪ And now you're back ♪

35:11.442 --> 35:13.110
♪ From outer space ♪

35:13.194 --> 35:15.321
♪ I just walked in
to find you there ♪

35:15.404 --> 35:17.323
♪ With that sad look
upon your face ♪

35:17.406 --> 35:19.492
♪ I should have changed
that stupid lock ♪

35:19.575 --> 35:21.619
♪ I should have made you
leave your key ♪

35:21.702 --> 35:23.788
♪ If I'd have known
for just one second ♪

35:23.871 --> 35:25.665
♪ You'd be back to bother me ♪

35:25.748 --> 35:27.667
♪ Go on, now, go ♪

35:27.750 --> 35:29.669
♪ Walk out the door ♪

35:29.752 --> 35:31.754
♪ Just turn around now ♪

35:31.838 --> 35:34.590
♪ 'Cause you're not welcome
anymore ♪

35:34.674 --> 35:38.052
♪ Weren't you the one who tried
to crush me with goodbye? ♪

35:38.135 --> 35:40.096
♪ Did you think I'd crumble? ♪

35:40.179 --> 35:42.181
- I'm going out for some air.

35:42.265 --> 35:44.141
- ♪ Oh, no, not I ♪

35:44.225 --> 35:46.310
♪ I will survive ♪

35:46.394 --> 35:49.313
[people shouting]

35:49.397 --> 35:52.483
[muffled singing]

36:04.745 --> 36:07.582
[soft melancholy music]

36:07.665 --> 36:14.755
♪ ♪

36:26.642 --> 36:29.186
♪ And I spent
oh, so many nights ♪

36:29.270 --> 36:31.105
♪ Feeling sorry
for myself ♪

36:31.188 --> 36:33.149
♪ I used to cry ♪

36:33.232 --> 36:35.276
♪ But now I hold my head
up high ♪

36:35.359 --> 36:37.194
♪ And you see me ♪

36:37.278 --> 36:38.654
♪ Somebody blue-- ♪

36:38.738 --> 36:39.947
- Give us a song, Alfie!

36:40.031 --> 36:41.657
- No, no, no, no, no, no.
I'm not singing.

36:41.741 --> 36:43.618
All right, give us a minute.
Give us a minute.

36:43.701 --> 36:44.827
[music cuts off]

36:44.911 --> 36:47.121
Now we've got some decisions
to make.

36:47.204 --> 36:48.497
[panting]

36:48.581 --> 36:50.249
Now, that looney mob out there
are not stopping,

36:50.333 --> 36:52.001
and I'm not sure they will.

36:52.084 --> 36:54.211
So I think we should
get out of there.

36:54.295 --> 36:56.464
Requisition a bus
and head for the countryside.

36:56.547 --> 36:57.632
Who's up for it?

36:57.715 --> 37:00.092
[crowd murmurs in agreement]

37:01.052 --> 37:03.262
All right, that's sorted then.

37:04.597 --> 37:06.307
And one other thing.

37:06.390 --> 37:07.975
[clears throat]

37:08.059 --> 37:09.477
Sandra.

37:09.560 --> 37:12.021
I've got something
to say to you.

37:12.104 --> 37:13.981
Now, I need to say it
in front of these witnesses

37:14.065 --> 37:15.733
so that you'll listen
and believe me.

37:18.319 --> 37:21.322
Now, I know you've got
the hump on me, and rightly so.

37:21.405 --> 37:23.366
I've been a right bastard
over the years.

37:23.449 --> 37:24.659
- Yeah, that's...

37:25.493 --> 37:28.162
- And I know you don't think
I can change, but I can.

37:28.245 --> 37:30.081
I have changed.
[crowd murmurs]

37:30.164 --> 37:32.500
All right, don't take the piss.
This is serious.

37:32.583 --> 37:34.669
Here.
[microphone feedback]

37:34.752 --> 37:36.837
Look, I've changed, Sandra.

37:37.797 --> 37:39.048
Now, I haven't the time

37:39.131 --> 37:42.009
to tell you how or why
right now, but...

37:42.093 --> 37:45.137
what I do wanna say is...

37:45.221 --> 37:48.349
Sandra Onslow...

37:48.432 --> 37:50.059
will you marry me?

37:51.435 --> 37:54.480
Now. Today.

37:54.563 --> 37:57.483
[dramatic music]

37:57.566 --> 38:04.657
♪ ♪

38:07.743 --> 38:09.203
- Yeah.

38:09.286 --> 38:11.622
[both laugh]

38:11.706 --> 38:14.875
Yeah.
[cheers and applause]

38:28.472 --> 38:30.141
[glass shattering]

38:30.224 --> 38:34.562
- ♪ Morning has broken ♪

38:34.645 --> 38:38.232
♪ Like the first morning ♪

38:38.315 --> 38:39.734
[grunting]

38:39.817 --> 38:42.570
♪ Blackbird has spoken ♪

38:42.653 --> 38:45.197
♪ Like the first bird ♪

38:45.281 --> 38:46.657
♪ ♪

38:46.741 --> 38:48.534
♪ Praise for them singing ♪

38:48.617 --> 38:50.619
- Excuse us.

38:50.703 --> 38:52.788
Is Mary here?

38:52.872 --> 38:54.915
She wasn't at home.

38:54.999 --> 38:57.001
- ♪ Praise
for them springing ♪

38:57.084 --> 38:58.586
- Lieutenant Giers speaking.
How can I help you?

38:58.669 --> 39:00.921
- This is General Thursday.

39:01.005 --> 39:03.340
Prepare a missile
for engagement.

39:03.424 --> 39:04.592
- Very good, sir.

39:04.675 --> 39:07.595
- Target, 10-40 Alpha.

39:07.678 --> 39:09.138
- But General,
that's Downing Street.

39:09.221 --> 39:11.599
- I know it's Downing Street,
damn you!

39:11.682 --> 39:15.311
- ♪ Sweet
the rain's new fall ♪

39:15.394 --> 39:19.315
♪ Sunlit from heaven ♪

39:19.398 --> 39:23.402
♪ Like the first dew fall ♪

39:23.486 --> 39:26.238
[people shouting]
♪ On the first grass ♪

39:26.322 --> 39:27.656
♪ ♪

39:27.740 --> 39:31.368
♪ Praise for the sweetness ♪
- Sandra!

39:31.452 --> 39:33.287
- Sandra!

39:33.370 --> 39:35.164
- Come on, come on.
Go. Ready?

39:35.247 --> 39:36.749
- Yeah.
- Okay.

39:36.832 --> 39:39.627
- Go, go!
- ♪ Sprung in completeness ♪

39:39.710 --> 39:42.421
♪ Where his feet pass ♪

39:42.505 --> 39:44.173
- Do not stop.

39:44.256 --> 39:47.551
♪ ♪

39:47.635 --> 39:49.011
- On you get.

39:49.095 --> 39:50.137
On you get.

39:50.221 --> 39:53.015
[knocking on door]

39:57.436 --> 39:58.479
- What the fuck?

39:58.562 --> 40:01.607
- ♪ Mine is the sunlight ♪

40:01.690 --> 40:03.109
- Thank you.
- Hi.

40:03.192 --> 40:06.445
- ♪ Mine is the morning ♪
- [laughs]

40:08.072 --> 40:10.783
- ♪ Born of the one light ♪

40:10.866 --> 40:13.911
♪ Eden saw play ♪
[jet roars]

40:13.994 --> 40:15.246
♪ ♪

40:15.329 --> 40:19.166
♪ Praise with elation ♪

40:19.250 --> 40:23.546
♪ Praise every morning ♪

40:23.629 --> 40:25.714
- Dearly beloved,

40:25.798 --> 40:30.427
we are gathered here today
to witness and celebrate

40:30.511 --> 40:32.888
the wedding
of these two people.

40:32.972 --> 40:35.891
They will publicly affirm
their bonds here

40:35.975 --> 40:39.562
in front of family and friends,
old and new.

40:39.645 --> 40:42.273
♪ ♪

40:42.356 --> 40:43.732
[phone beeps]

40:43.816 --> 40:46.193
- Stop plaguing me!

40:46.277 --> 40:47.695
Damn you!

40:47.778 --> 40:50.156
[tense music]

40:50.239 --> 40:51.490
♪ ♪

40:51.574 --> 40:53.117
[phone chimes]

40:53.200 --> 40:54.785
- God have mercy on us.

40:54.869 --> 40:57.621
♪ ♪

40:57.705 --> 41:01.792
Go to final stage,
target confirmed.

41:01.876 --> 41:03.544
♪ ♪

41:03.627 --> 41:06.755
[jet engine roaring]

41:11.635 --> 41:13.471
[jet engine roaring]
[rumbling]

41:13.554 --> 41:16.473
[air raid siren wailing]

41:20.352 --> 41:22.062
- ♪ Morning has broken ♪

41:22.146 --> 41:24.064
- If anyone knows
of any just cause

41:24.148 --> 41:26.317
why they may not
be joined together,

41:26.400 --> 41:29.028
speak now
or forever hold your peace.

41:30.112 --> 41:34.158
Sandra Onslow,
do you take Alfred Pennyworth

41:34.241 --> 41:36.035
to be your lawful
wedded husband?

41:37.661 --> 41:40.581
- ♪ Praise for the singing ♪

41:40.664 --> 41:41.749
- I do.

41:41.832 --> 41:44.168
- ♪ Praise for the morning ♪

41:44.251 --> 41:47.671
- Alfred Pennyworth,
do you take Sandra Onslow

41:47.755 --> 41:49.924
to be--
[explosion booms]

41:50.007 --> 41:53.093
- ♪ Fresh from the word ♪

41:53.177 --> 41:54.929
- Fucking hell.

41:55.012 --> 42:02.102
♪ ♪

42:08.150 --> 42:11.111
[adventurous music]

42:11.195 --> 42:18.285
♪ ♪
